Dear AID India Volunteers,

Daan Utsav is India's festival of Giving which is celebrated
between October 2nd and 8th every year. More than million people across the
country participate in doing an act of giving and experience the pure joy
of giving. Every year AID India provides it's volunteers an opportunity to
celebrate the festival with some of our events. You can donate your time as
a volunteer and experience the joy of giving :-) and have a #happydot after
contributing.

We are currently looking for volunteers for the following events. Sign up
for any one of the event if you wish to participate :-).. For more idea's
and information, do write to aid.selva@gmail.com / Whatsapp - 9790951652

Volunteer for #MuRail - a project to beautify some of our railway
stations. This #DaanUtsav many group of volunteers collectively are going
to beautify Railway Stations in Chennai with Mural Art work. We have got
permission to beautify 23 stations. AID India and Bhumi will
together paint 4 stations (Guindy, Fort, Triplicane and Mundakanni Amman
Street). If you wish to volunteer sign up here.
Sign up for Railway Station Painting
<https://goo.gl/forms/ogd99FqYbYySJKQm2>

Volunteer at IOC Fuel stations to conduct simple activities with the
customers and help us collect stationary materials. This #DaanUtsav several
IOC Fuel stations will provide space for NGO's to have a desk and conduct
activities. We have got permission to have stalls at 5 stations. If you
wish to volunteer sign up here. We will have small orientation regarding
the activities to do :-)
Sign up to Volunteer at IOC fuel station
<https://goo.gl/forms/8bVZssEpDQpV8lZj1>

Volunteer at Chennai Metro Rail stations to conduct simple activities with
the commuters and help us collect stationary and sports materials. This
#DaanUtsav CMRL has provide space for AID India to have an activity desk
and conduct activities at 7 of their metro stations. . If you wish to
volunteer sign up here. We will have small orientation regarding the
activities to do :-)
Sign up to Volunteer at CMRL station
<https://goo.gl/forms/S3kWbvLQ6x5ornt83>
